<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2895] MockRandomCodec loads termsIndex even if termsIndexDivisor is set to -1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2895</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;When working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2891&quot; title=&quot;IndexWriterConfig does not allow readerTermsIndexDivisor to be -1, while the latest indicates the terms index should not be loaded&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2891&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (on trunk), I found out that if MockRandomCodec is used, then setting IWC.readerTermsIndexDivisor to -1 allows seeking e.g., termDocs, when it shouldn&apos;t. Other Codecs fail to seek, as expected by the test. We need to find out why MockRandomCodec does not fail as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To verify that, run &quot;ant test-core -Dtestcase=TestIndexWriterReader -Dtestmethod=testNoTermsIndex -Dtests.codec=MockRandom&quot;, but comment out the line which adds MockRandom to the list of illegal codecs in the test.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
